@robertsmith4681 The average concentration of gold in seawater is about 1 to 2 parts per trillion, or 0.001 to 0.002 milligrams per cubic meter. 

Approximately 0.0015 milligrams of gold is contained in a cubic meter of ocean water, based on the average concentration range of 1 to 2 ppt.

